XmtUJolOJD0.title: GLUTE ACTIVATION ROUTINE | Booty Growth
XmtUJolOJD0.description:
This is my go-to Glute Activation routine 🔥 I’m using a DB Booty Band to add extra resistance and increase glute activation, available from: https://dannibelle.com/collections/fitness-equipment/products/db-booty-band-pack

Glute activation is the process of preparing your glutes to perform and fire during exercise. Without proper glute activation, you may find that your surrounding muscles are utilised during glute targeted exercises to support your movement and compensate for the lack of glute engagement. Glute activation is usually achieved through a series of effective warm up exercises so here are a few of my favs that you can incorporate into your routine!

More info on glute activation: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zg4wvNpjt34&t=72s

ACTIVATION ROUTINE 

2 SETS 

- 10 x Lateral Band Walk (Up & Back)
- 20 x Glute Bridge 
- 12 x Seated Abduction/12 x Pulse 
- 15 x Fire Hydrants (each leg)
- 12 x Step Squats

DjgngmJIL8M.title: 15 MINUTE HIIT WORKOUT + HEALTHY MUFFIN RECIPE
DjgngmJIL8M.description:
You can have your muffin and eat it too. In fact it's encouraged because these muffins are the perfect engine starter fuelling a 15 minute HIIT Workout or as a quick, easy and convenient post-workout snack. Today we're baking, we're skipping and we're working up a sweat. Give this 15 minute fat burner workout a try and get amongst this muffin recipe! Hope you enjoy this video, workout and recipe below.

WORKOUT: 

15 Minutes 

4 SETS, 60 - 90 seconds rest between sets

- 30 sec Standard Skipping 
- 30 sec Mountain Climbers 
- 30 sec High Knee Skipping 
- 30 sec Squat w/ Knee Tap
- 30 sec Star Skips 
- 30 sec Bicycle Crunches (V-Sit Bicycles)


MUFFINS RECIPE: 


INGREDIENTS

1 1/2 cups Rolled Oats
1/2 cup Almond Milk
3/4 cup Wholemeal Flour
2 tbsp Vanilla Whey Protein Powder
2 tsp Baking Powder
1/2 tsp Baking Soda
¾ cup Dates, chopped
½ cup Walnuts, chopped
1 egg, beaten
4 tbsp Grape Seed Oil
2 tbsp Rice Malt Syrup
1/3 cup Prune Juice
1 ripe Banana, mashed

METHOD
1. Preheat oven to 200˚C and lightly grease
muffin tray
2. Combine oats and milk in a medium
bowl and allow to soak for approximately
10 minutes
3. In a separate large bowl mix flour, whey
protein, baking powder, baking soda, dates
and walnuts
4. In another bowl combine egg, oil, rice malt
syrup and prune juice and then add to oats
mixture. Stir until well combined. Add flour
mix and mashed banana
5. Spoon batter into prepared muffin tray.
Bake for 10 – 15 minutes or until
golden brown

IhUq7X3sdH8.title: HOW TO GROW YOUR BOOTY - Tips + Glute Workout | Dannibelle
IhUq7X3sdH8.description:
Today we discuss all things booty & glute growth! 

Programs & Booty Bands: www.dannibelle.com

Glutes, bum, booty, backside, peach, cake, many terms have been coined to describe this muscle but what actually are your glutes? The gluteal muscles (glutes) are a group of three muscles which make up the buttocks: the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius and gluteus minimus. In recent times, boasting a large posterior has become a desirable target for many but how do we actually grow our glute muscles? Well here are my top 5 tips for creating the ultimate booty.

WORKOUT:

Glute Activation:

2 SETS

- 5 x Lateral Band Walk (up & back)
- 15 x Glute Bridges
- 10 x Abduction/10 x Pulses 
- 12 x Step Squats

BOOTY WORKOUT:

3 SETS

10 - 12 Hip Thrusts
10 - 12 Bulgarian Split Squats (each leg)
10 - 12 Goblet Squats
10 - 12 Single Leg Hip Thrusts (each leg)
10 - 12 Sumo Deadlifts

FINISHER: 

2 SETS

- 30 x Frog Pumps
- 20 x Squat Pulses

Sample testing is such an important part of the process in creating an activewear brand. In this video I test the DB Active samples and put them through the following product quality tests:

- Squat test: Making sure the leggings are "Squat proof" meaning that they aren't see-through during exercise.
- Sweat test: Making sure the fabric is as sweat-wicking as possible. 
- Cardio test: Making sure the waistband on the leggings is tight enough to stay put during cardio.
